# Public, checked-in environment overrides for the upstream nix-openclaw gateway.
# Keep secrets out of this file.
#
# Minimal deployable pass:
# - network exposure is controlled in Nix via `gateway.bind = "tailnet"`
# - the gateway auth token is generated locally on first start under
#   `/var/lib/openclaw/secrets/gateway-token.env`
# - external credentials (provider keys, Telegram token, etc.) stay out of this
#   file and should come from a separate secret env file when actually needed
#
# This file intentionally stays almost empty until a documented non-secret
# upstream environment variable is genuinely needed.
